        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 3:26PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 326 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 11 miles west of Hereford to near
LaSalle, or extending from 42 miles north of Greeley to 10 miles
south of Greeley, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree branches and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eastern Greeley, Evans, LaSalle, Kersey, Gilcrest, Grover,
Briggsdale, Barnesville, Keota, Purcell, Gill, Galeton, Riverside
Reservoir, Hereford, Jackson Reservoir, Orchard, Pawnee Buttes,
Garden City, Cornish and Hardin.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Blowing dust can also be expected.
Secure loose objects and move to a safe shelter inside a building or
vehicle.</instruction>
